<HEADLINE>
Jefferson, Turkoglu earn NBA weekly honors
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, Jan. 28 (Xinhua)
</P>
<P>
Minnesota's Al Jefferson and Orlando's Hedo Turkoglu were
selected the Eastern and Western Conference's players of the
week, respectively, for the week ending January 27, NBA announced
Monday.
</P>
<P>
Jefferson led the Timberwolves to a 3-1 week, averaging 28.8
points and 12.8 rebounds. The team defeated three playoff teams
from last season and its lone loss came by just a point against
the league's best team, Boston. His high point was a 40-point,
19-rebound effort in a 98-95 win Sunday over New Jersey.
</P>
<P>
Turkoglu helped the Magic to a 3-1 week, including wins over
Eastern Conference leaders Detroit and Boston. He led Orlando in
scoring each of its four games last week and averaged 25.5 points
a game. Turkoglu tallied a game-high 27 points, including the
game-winning three-pointer at the buzzer in a 96-93 victory
Sunday over Boston.
</P>
